1. Let's go back in history
Researchers first used RNNs for NLP.
Sentence :I love deep learningRNN Output
The RNN processes one word at a time. I → love → deep → learning
Everything seemed fine.
2. Then people found a problem
Suppose we have
"The movie that I watched yesterday with my friends was fantastic."
When the RNN reaches fantastic, it needs to remember
movie
because fantastic describes the movie.
But between them are many words.
movie
 ↓
that I watched yesterday with my friends was fantastic
The information has to travel through many time steps.
After many steps,
•	information becomes weak 
•	gradients vanish 
•	long-term dependencies are hard to learn 
This is the long dependency problem.
3. LSTM solved part of it
LSTM introduced
•	Forget Gate 
•	Input Gate 
•	Output Gate 
•	Cell State 
The cell state acts like a memory.
Word1
   ↓
Cell State
   ↓
Word2
   ↓
Cell State
   ↓
Word3
Now the model can remember information much longer.
Great improvement!
4. But LSTM still had problems
Even though LSTM remembers better,
it still processes words like this
I

↓

love

↓

deep

↓

learning
Everything is sequential.
The next word cannot start until the previous word is processed.
So training becomes slow.
________________________________________
Another problem
Suppose the sentence has 80 words.
To relate
Word 1

↓

Word 80
information must still travel through many LSTM cells.
Even LSTMs struggle with very long sequences.
________________________________________
5. Bahdanau Attention helped
Now researchers said
Instead of forcing the decoder to depend on only one final encoder state,
let the decoder look back at all encoder hidden states.
Decoder

↓

h1 h2 h3 h4 h5
Now while generating each word,
the decoder focuses on the important encoder outputs.
This greatly improved machine translation.
6. But another question appeared
Attention only helped during decoding.
What about the encoder?
The encoder was still
Word1Word2Word3Word4
It was still an LSTM.
It still had to process sequentially.
So researchers asked:
Can we remove the RNN completely?
This question led to Self-Attention.
________________________________________
7. The main idea of Self-Attention
Instead of passing information through many hidden states,
why not let every word directly communicate with every other word?
Instead of
Word1Word2Word3Word4
Use: Word1 ↔ Word2
Word1 ↔ Word3
Word1 ↔ Word4

Word2 ↔ Word3
Word2 ↔ Word4

Word3 ↔ Word4
Every word can "talk" to every other word.
No long chain is needed.
This is the core idea of self-attention:
self-attention is used in many tasks besides next-word prediction:
•	Machine Translation 
•	Text Classification 
•	Sentiment Analysis 
•	Question Answering 
•	Named Entity Recognition 
•	Summarization 
•	Next-word prediction (GPT) 
So predicting the next word is one application, not the definition of self-attention.
Self-attention allows every word to look at every other word in the same sentence and decide which words are most important for understanding its meaning.
8. Example
Sentence
The animal didn't cross the road because it was tired.
When processing
it
the model asks
Which word helps me understand "it"?
Instead of relying on memory,
it directly looks at
The
animal
didn't
cross
road
because
it
was
tired
It may assign a high weight to
animal
So
it↓animal
This direct connection is much easier than remembering through many hidden states.
10. How does it know which words are important?
This is where Query, Key, and Value come in.
Every word embedding creates
EmbeddingQuery (Q),Key (K),Value (V)
Every word gets three vectors.
For example:
love=Qlove,Klove,Vlove
QueryCompare with KeysFind best matchesReturn corresponding Values
Self-attention works in a similar way.
12. Computing attention
Suppose we are processing
love
Its Query is
Qlove
Now compare it with every Key.
Qlove • KI
Qlove • Klove
Qlove • Kdeep
Qlove • Klearning
These dot products measure similarity.
Example
2.1,4.8,3.7,0.5
Higher score
↓
More related.
13. Softmax
Convert the scores into probabilities.
Softmax
0.08,0.55,0.30,0.07
Now all the weights sum to 1
14. Weighted sum
Now multiply the weights with the Value vectors.
0.08 × VI+0.55 × Vlove+0.30 × Vdeep+0.07 × Vlearning
The result is the new representation of "love", now enriched with information from the whole sentence.
15. Why is Self-Attention better?
RNN
Word1↓Word2↓Word3↓Word4
Information flows step by step.
________________________________________
Self-Attention
Word1 ↔ Word2,Word1 ↔ Word3,Word1 ↔ Word4,Word2 ↔ Word3,Word2 ↔ Word4,
Word3 ↔ Word4
Every word can directly interact with every other word.
________________________________________
16. Advantages
✅ Captures long-range dependencies
First word-Last word
No long memory chain is needed.
________________________________________
✅ Parallel computation
RNN
Word1Word2Word3
Cannot compute Word3 until Word2 finishes.
Self-attention
Word1,Word2,Word3,Word4
All attention scores can be computed at the same time on GPUs, making training much faster.
17. One limitation
Self-attention by itself does not know word order.
For example:
Dog bites man.
and
Man bites dog.
contain the same words but different meanings.
Self-attention alone sees only the set of embeddings and their relationships. It needs additional information about positions.
Before Self-Attention
A typical Seq2Seq model looked like this:
Input Sentence
Embeddings
LSTM / GRU / RNN Encoder
Hidden States
Bahdanau Attention
LSTM Decoder
Output Sentence
Notice that both the encoder and decoder use RNN/LSTM.
After Self-Attention (Transformer)
The architecture becomes:
Input Sentence
      ▼
Embedding
      ▼
Positional Encoding
      ▼
Self-Attention
      ▼
Feed Forward Network
      ▼
Output
There is no RNN.
There is no LSTM.
Self-attention becomes the mechanism that models relationships between words.
Why could RNN/LSTM be removed?
To understand learning, the information from I has to pass through multiple LSTM steps.
With self-attention:
             learning
          ↙    ↓     ↘
         I    love   deep
The word learning can directly access information from every other word in a single attention computation.
There is no need for hidden states traveling through time.
Does Self-Attention completely replace LSTM?
Inside a Transformer, yes.
Transformers do not use RNN or LSTM layers for sequence modeling.
Instead, they use:
•	Self-Attention 
•	Feed Forward Networks 
•	Positional Encoding 
•	Residual Connections 
•	Layer Normalization
Does that mean LSTMs are obsolete?
Not completely.
LSTMs are still used in some situations:
•	Small datasets 
•	Time-series forecasting 
•	Embedded or edge devices with limited resources 
•	Legacy systems 
However, for modern NLP, Transformers have largely replaced LSTMs.
Examples include:
•	BERT 
•	GPT 
•	T5 
These models are built on Transformer architectures rather than RNNs or LSTMs.
One important point
Self-attention does not replace the entire neural network.
It only replaces the sequence-processing part that RNNs and LSTMs used to perform.
For example:
